(15, '&lt;div class=&quot;zQfo7b&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 48px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87); font-family: Roboto, RobotoDraft, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;gDeJqe&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: &amp;quot;Google Sans&amp;quot;, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1.375rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.75rem; color: rgb(32, 33, 36); margin-bottom: 8px;&quot;&gt;What happened to Google+?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;GIqPVe&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; letter-spacing: 0.00625em; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.5rem; color: rgb(60, 64, 67);&quot;&gt;In December 2018, we&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://blog.google/technology/safety-security/expediting-changes-google-plus/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(41, 98, 255);&quot;&gt;announced&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;our decision to shut down Google+ for consumers in April 2019.&lt;div class=&quot;hPLqfc&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; height: 8px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Other Google products (such as Gmail, Google Photos, Google Drive and YouTube) were not shut down as part of the consumer Google+ shutdown and you can continue using these products. The Google Account that you use to sign in to these services will remain. Please note that photos and videos already backed up in Google Photos will not be deleted.&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://support.google.com/plus/answer/9217723?hl=en_GB&amp;amp;authuser=0&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(41, 98, 255);&quot;&gt;Learn more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;zQfo7b&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 48px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87); font-family: Roboto, Roboto